# Card-audit (mtg-948 Part B): Icy Manipulator — activated tap ability (scripted).
#
# Closed issue mtg-511 closed Icy Manipulator as WORKING but carried NO scripted
# puzzle with semantic assertions. This audit puzzle SCRIPTS the activated
# ability and asserts the tap-target outcome.
#
# Icy Manipulator is a {4} Artifact: "{1}, {T}: Tap target artifact, creature, or
# land." (A:AB$ Tap | Cost$ 1 T | ValidTgts$ Artifact,Creature,Land). Activating
# it pays {1} and taps Icy itself, then taps the chosen target permanent (CR
# 602, 701.21). This puzzle asserts the ability is usable and the artifact's tap
# does not destroy or move its target (a "soft" lock, not removal).
#
# Aspects exercised (issue mtg-511):
#   1. The {1}{T} activated ability is offered and activatable (a non-creature
#      artifact's repeatable activated ability).
#   2. ValidTgts$ Artifact,Creature,Land accepts an opponent's untapped creature.
#   3. The tap effect leaves the target on the battlefield (it taps, does not
#      destroy): P1 still controls the Grizzly Bears afterward, and P0 still
#      controls Icy Manipulator. No creature died.
#
# Scenario:
#   - P0: Icy Manipulator + 1 untapped Island (to pay the {1}) on the
#     battlefield.
#   - P1: an untapped Grizzly Bears (2/2) it controls.
#   - Script: P0 activates Icy Manipulator targeting the Grizzly Bears; it taps.

[metadata]
Name:Card Audit - Icy Manipulator Taps a Target
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 scripts Icy Manipulator's {1}{T} ability at P1's Grizzly Bears, tapping it. Both Icy and the Bears stay on the battlefield (tap, not removal). Backs issue mtg-511 (AB$ Tap Cost$ 1 T over ValidTgts$ Artifact,Creature,Land; CR 701.21).

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=
p0battlefield=Icy Manipulator;Island
p0library=Island;Island;Island;Island;Island

p1life=20
p1battlefield=Grizzly Bears
p1library=Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest

[p0_script]
# Activate Icy Manipulator's tap ability at P1's Grizzly Bears (the only legal
# creature; pays {1} from the Island and taps Icy as part of the cost). Then PASS
# for the rest of the game so the board stays frozen (no combat / new plays),
# keeping the membership assertions durable.
activate Icy Manipulator targeting Grizzly Bears
PASS_UNTIL turn=5,phase=MAIN1

[p1_script]
# P1 takes no proactive action: it never attacks with the tapped Bears (a tapped
# creature cannot attack anyway) and plays nothing, so the board is stable.
PASS_UNTIL turn=5,phase=MAIN1

[assertions]
# Icy Manipulator is still on P0's battlefield after activating (the ability taps
# it as a cost; it is not sacrificed/removed). Durable: P0 passes, so nothing
# moves it.
battlefield contains Icy Manipulator
# The tapped target stayed on P1's battlefield — Icy TAPS, it does not destroy.
# Durable: P1 passes and a tapped creature cannot attack, so the Bears never
# leaves the battlefield.
opponent battlefield contains Grizzly Bears
# No creature died from the tap effect (a soft lock, not removal).
NOT creature died Grizzly Bears
